00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:30,080
(Her Private Life)

3
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:33,320
(Final Episode)

4
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,520
Mom!

5
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:01,040
Duk-mi's scribbling again!

6
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,000
I'm not scribbling! I'm drawing!

7
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,040
Well, it looks like scribbling to me,

8
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:09,000
so I'm calling it scribbling!

9
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:11,040
Hey!

10
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,360
Mom!

11
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:15,840
Duk-mi,

12
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,520
I told you not to hit Eun-ki!

13
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,480
I said you'd be in trouble if you scribbled again, didn't I?

14
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:37,240
This isn't scribbling!

15
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:39,800
Sung Duk-mi, just what are you??

16
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,680
What are you going to be when you grow up?

17
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:44,280
An painter who draws art!

18
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:47,120
I'm going to fill a big gallery with my art.

19
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:54,200
Hey, stop it!

20
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,440
Stop, stop!

21
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:57,320
- Hey! - Stop it!

22
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,160
Don't!

23
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,880
Did you have a good dream?

24
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
I did. A dream that was good because it's a memory.

25
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,760
But it was a little sad at the same time, too.

26
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:17,840
I was playing with Yun-je, Eun-ki and Duk-su.

27
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,360
What have you been doing since you woke up?

28
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:36,200
I've been drawing.

29
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,000
Drawing your sleeping face.

30
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,400
Did you make me look pretty?

31
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:46,520
Your beauty is rather surreal,

32
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,680
so it's quite hard to convey it on paper.

33
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,360
In my dream,

34
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,760
I was drawing with Yun-je.

35
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:03,440
We were drawing with chalk, absolutely everywhere.

36
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:08,440
But then Eun-ki said he was going to tell on us for scribbling.

37
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,800
So I told him,

38
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,880
"I'm going to become a painter someday,

39
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:14,120
and my art is going to be hung in art galleries."

40
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:19,440
Though I didn't end up being a painter,

41
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:21,840
I did become someone who hangs paintings.

42
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,480
"When we visit an exhibition today,

43
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:35,320
we are not directly observing works of art.

44
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:41,160
What we are observing is the curator's notion of what art is.

45
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,040
In short??

46
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,880
The ultimate artist is not the producer

47
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:49,640
but the curator, his activity of selection."

48
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,080
Slavoj Zizek?

49
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,160
I wholly agree with him.

50
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,160
Curators are artists, too.

51
00:04:58,160 --> 00:05:01,040
You even made me draw again,

52
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,480
Curator Sung Duk-mi.

53
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:06,840
The exhibition hall is my canvas.

54
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,360
But you know??

55
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,880
Right now, I feel like

56
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:18,400
your face is my canvas.

57
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,160
My I draw some pictures?

58
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:25,760
What will you draw with?

59
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,440
I'm really motivated to get creative right now.

60
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,080
How should I draw?

61
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,200
Shall I try?

62
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,560
Alright, shall we start painting our canvas, then?

63
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,840
What? Canvas?

64
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:52,080
Let's first head over to Mr. Noh Seok's collection.

65
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:52,920
Sure.

66
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,160
- Alright. - Alright.

67
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,000
- Did you check everything? - Yes.

68
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,640
Okay! Make sure they're tuned into

69
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,080
channel two at all times.

70
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,040
Okay, and as for the microphone??

71
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,480
Always check the volume.

72
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,840
Ah, ah. Yes, it's working.

73
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,200
C E G!

74
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,840
Welcome to Cheum's 5th Anniversary Exhibition!

75
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,920
About this much?

76
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,800
Just a little more to the right.

77
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,640
Is this okay?

78
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,920
It's crooked! Lower the right side a little more.

79
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,160
Miss Hyo-jin, please hurry!

80
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,080
Yes, yes. I'm done.

81
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,160
Done, done, done!

82
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,400
- Great. - Nice!

83
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,560
That looks great.

84
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,560
I know.

85
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,440
Nine??

86
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,040
- Let's check the projector. - Sure.

87
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,040
- Has the brightness been set? - Yes.

88
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,120
So it should look brighter once the lights are dimmed?

89
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,200
Yes.

90
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,440
Cheum's 5th Anniversary Special Exhibition,

91
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:35,120
THE ROOM THE LIFE.

92
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,840
Today's finally our opening day!

93
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:39,480
Hyo-jin, this is your first exhibition. How are you feeling?

94
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,040
I've got butterflies.

95
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:44,800
It's as if I'm meeting someone I've only imagined.

96
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,960
It was such hard work,

97
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,120
but still??I'm excited.

98
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,000
Are you sure it's not because you'll be seeing Mr. Cha Si-an?

99
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Ah, you got me.

100
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,440
So, Director Gold.

101
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,640
How did you come up with the title?

102
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:04,120
I was inspired by someone's room.

103
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,160
Why, what was their room like?

104
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,520
It was inspiring and fun.

105
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:11,160
And filled with much happiness.

106
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:24,560
"Fill your room with things you love

107
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,360
so that your life can become much happier."

108
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,000
We're finally the first ones here!

109
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,120
Finally the first ones!

110
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,240
I can't wait for them to open up.

111
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,440
What kind of art will there be? Photos?

112
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:45,200
Mr. Cha Si-an, could you face the front, please?

113
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,120
- Thank you. - Look this way for us, too.

114
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:49,280
This way, too.

115
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,200
- How do you feel? - Wave to us, please!

116
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,760
I'm feeling very good.

117
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:55,000
Mr. Cha Si-an, smile for us.

118
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,400
- This way. - That's great!

119
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,080
- That's great. - This way. Over here!

120
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,920
That's great.

121
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,760
Oh my God!

122
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:06,880
Hyo-jin?

123
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,160
That person over there??

124
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,240
Is he a sculpture on display?

125
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,040
Si-an does look like a sculpture, doesn't he?

126
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,480
He's so handsome!

127
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,080
Secretary Kim? Give it, give it, give it!

128
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,840
Oh my God!

129
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,080
Hyo-jin?

130
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:39,760
Isn't that what you designed?

131
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,800
Mom.

132
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,640
Yeah, what is it?

133
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:49,920
I could just die right now.

134
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,840
No, no, no! You can't die just yet, Hyo-jin!

135
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,440
Don't say such a terrible thing.

136
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:56,480
Oh my God! Hyo-jin, I'm so proud of you.

137
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,040
As incredible as we say art is,

138
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,040
could it be more so than living people?

139
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:37,000
No matter how pathetic I may be,

140
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:40,280
I'm far more superb than those haughty paintings

141
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,640
hanging up on that wall.

142
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:46,080
Because I'm still here, alive and living.

143
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,840
(Roh Seok)

144
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:59,520
These eyes??They're not speaking of sadness

145
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,080
before a farewell, or of enlightenment before death.

146
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,760
He's staring at the person he loves.

147
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,800
That's what he wanted to leave behind:

148
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,680
this gaze directed towards that person.

149
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:11,440
It's his greeting to that person.

150
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,480
"Hello, I'm still here."

151
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:18,160
"I'm always here, looking at you."

152
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,440
Hello.

153
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:28,840
(Hello)

154
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:45,320
Soap bubbles, rocking horse, ferris wheel, pirate ship??

155
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:48,600
They're all things that a child might like.

156
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:53,600
I think I know what feeling she put into these paintings.

157
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,000
We're smiling.

158
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,600
Both of us.

159
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,440
Very happily.

160
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,720
(Fill your room with things you love)

161
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:26,200
(so that your life will become much happier)

162
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:30,000
(THE ROOM, THE LIFE)

163
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,800
Congratulations, Mom.

164
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,400
It's your first exhibition.

165
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,560
Thank you, Si-an.

166
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,360
And thank you to you too, Yun-je.

167
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,840
Thank you, Ms. Lee Sol,

168
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:16,000
for letting us exhibit your valuable works.

169
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,240
Thank you, Curator Sung Duk-mi.

170
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,560
Congratulations.

171
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:32,880
Um??May I take a picture for you?

172
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,920
- Let's take one. - Yes.

173
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:40,000
Duk-mi just happens to be a great photographer.

174
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,960
Would you like to order?

175
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,880
- I'll have an IA. - One IA,

176
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,640
and one condensed milk latte without the espresso shot.

177
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:09,200
You drink it without the espresso?

178
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,160
I can't drink coffee.

179
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,440
Since I take after a certain someone.

180
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,800
Then I'll have the same.

181
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,880
One condensed milk latte without the espresso shot.

182
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:21,120
What would you like, Mr. Cha Si-an?

183
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:23,040
Then I'll have the same thing as Curator Sung.

184
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:24,840
An iced americano.

185
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:28,640
Then that's two condensed milk lattes without the espresso,

186
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:30,360
one iced americano,

187
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:34,800
and one iced americano that's extra delicious.

188
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,000
Have you always been unable to drink coffee?

189
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,000
Ms. Lee, didn't you change your bias to me?

190
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,000
- Ju Hyuk. - Yes.

191
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,120
There may be an entrance to a fandom, but there's no exit.

192
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,640
A bias is a bias,

193
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:03,280
and Si-an's Si-an.

194
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,120
I guess you're not so interested.

195
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,520
Ms. Lee.

196
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,520
Yes, Mr. Cha Si-an.

197
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:16,080
What's this music that's playing now?

198
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,840
It's my first time hearing it.

199
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,400
The music's great, huh?

200
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,080
There's this band, FADE??

201
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:25,000
Oh, he's the vocalist and guitarist.

202
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,960
Ju Hyuk.

203
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:28,520
They're going to release an album soon, too.

204
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,560
I see. FADE??

205
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,560
It's great. I'll be looking forward to your album.

206
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:39,480
Once it's out, I'll gift one to you.

207
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,120
Directly, in person.

208
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:43,440
Yes, well then??

209
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,080
Ju Hyuk, please pinch me.

210
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:15,040
Let's go in first.

211
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,080
Let's go.

212
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,840
Hello, I'm Yun-je's mother.

213
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,200
When I heard you were coming,

214
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:42,040
I stayed up all night, thinking about what I should say.

215
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:44,520
But I still have nothing to say,

216
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:46,480
other than that I'm sorry.

217
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,160
Yun-je told me the whole story.

218
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:54,240
Thank you for looking after him with such loving care,

219
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,000
even if it was brief.

220
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:40,160
(Sung Duk-su)

221
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,520
So you were here, Duk-su.

222
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:51,160
When you were little, I once brought you here

223
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:54,040
with Eun-ki and Duk-su.

224
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:57,840
At that time, Duk-su saw one of the monks

225
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:59,840
and almost choked on his laughter.

226
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:02,480
He kept saying, "Baldie! Baldie!"

227
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:06,640
I was so embarrassed and so sorry.

228
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,000
That's why I brought him here.

229
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,720
So he could laugh all he wants.

230
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,720
I'll make you laugh, Mom.

231
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,160
I have something for you.

232
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:46,720
The pictures alone show how well you looked after him.

233
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,560
Yun-je looks like he's at ease.

234
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:56,040
Thankfully, he got along well with Duk-mi and Eun-ki.

235
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:57,760
He ate well, too.

236
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,680
(Heo Yun-je, 7 years old Mom, I miss you)

237
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,120
After sending Duk-su off,

238
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:18,040
I wasn't in my right mind.

239
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,160
When I finally came around??

240
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,560
He'd already been adopted.

241
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,920
So you went back??

242
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,640
To the orphanage where Yun-je was.

243
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:39,080
I should've gone a little sooner??

244
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:44,000
There aren't just one or two things I'm regretting.

245
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:50,120
I don't know how I can face you or Yun-je.

246
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:54,360
It's me who should be saying that.

247
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:57,320
But it was an accident. You didn't abandon him.

248
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:03,120
I have another son named Si-an.

249
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,280
The person who helped me search

250
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:08,120
after I lost Yun-je

251
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,040
is Si-an's dad.

252
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,480
"After losing your child,

253
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,440
how could you start a family like nothing happened

254
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,600
and live on?"

255
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:27,680
Yun-je could've despised me and chosen not to understand me,

256
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,760
but this is what he said:

257
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:32,760
He read that a wife who's lost her husband is a widow,

258
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:36,040
a husband who's lost his wife is a widower,

259
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:40,120
and a child who's lost his parents is an orphan.

260
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:43,440
But for parents who've lost their child??

261
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:52,080
the grief is so great that there's no name we can assign them.

262
00:20:55,840 --> 00:21:00,040
He told me no one has the right to point fingers at me

263
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:02,720
for making the decisions I did so that I could live on

264
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:07,160
and pull through those times.

265
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,840
So he told me not to be sorry.

266
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,760
So while it may be shameless of me??

267
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:24,200
I want to take that as Yun-je having forgiven me.

268
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,440
So Mrs. Sung, you too??

269
